<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-12-22T02:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-12-22T02:00:00-05:00" n="376" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d376">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/5871: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-12-22T15:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">December 22,
                                        1924—3 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received December 22—7:48
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>500. Legation’s 463, December 1, noon.<note n="28" xml:id="d376fn28">Not
                                printed.</note> Following sent commander in chief today: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“Legation’s November 30, 1 p.m. Referring to our recent
                                    conversations I perceive no objection to your withdrawing
                                    destroyers from North China waters.”</p></quote></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Schurman</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>